verbose_text: When identical GnTI proteins, fused to either YFP or CFP, were co-expressed in protoplasts, a high degree of co-localization to the same Golgi stacks was observed, indicating that the relatively high gene dosage that is used in the protoplast transfection assays does not lead to alternative targeting of differentially labeled proteins per se.
